U.N. Concerned about Continued Violence in Sierra Leone
UNITED NATIONS , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- The U.N. Security Council remains gravely concerned about the continued violence in Sierra Leone and on Thursday called for the immediate restoration of President Tejan Kabbah 's government .
The Council said in a presidential statement that it expressed its deep regret at the loss of life and property and immense suffering of the people of Sierra Leone since a military coup took place on May 25 , 1997 .
The Council commended the important role of the Economic Community of West African States ( ECOWAS ) for the peaceful solution of the crisis .
It encouraged the Military Observer Group of ECOWAS ( ECOMOG ) to proceed in its efforts to foster peace and stability in Sierra Leone .
It stressed the need for close cooperation between the legitimate government of Sierra Leone , ECOWAS , ECOMOG commanders , the special envoy of U.N. Secretary-General , U.N. agencies and relevant international bodies in their work .
The Council supported the idea of U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan to take rapid steps towards the reopening of the U.N. Liaison Office in the capital of Freedom in order to assist the national reconciliation and political dialogue in that country .
